    "body": "Hm I [have the same concerns as before](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/29083#discussion_r42522088) where if we start annotating reexports we may want to hammer down the semantics first. For example what does it mean to have a stable reexport of an unstable item? An unstable reexport of a stable item? I'd personally expect:\n- Stable reexport of stable -- ok, everything is stable\n- Unstable reexport of unstable -- ok, everything is unstable\n- Stable reexport of unstable -- compiler error\n- Unstable reexport of stable -- ok, unstable to reference via this name but stable to reference via the other name.\n",
