    "body": "> To move this forward, perhaps this could be included with the PR that actually verifies these attributes? It's pretty easy to skip past annotations like this in a review so it's not critical it be split out.\n\nSorry, I have linguistic difficulties with these two sentences.\nFirst, should attributes be verified in this PR, or new annotation added in some future PR? (I think, the latter). Second, what is not critical to be split out from what?\n\nAlso, what's about inheritance by default? (`use A as B;` inherits stability of `A` by default).\nCurrently, I tend to \"revert\" this PR and remove existing annotations on reexports, because they are all would be unnecessary with inheritance (in addition to being completely unchecked now).\n",
