    "body": "Ah sorry I'm not always the most eloquent person either! To answer your questions:\n\n> First, should attributes be verified in this PR, or new annotation added in some future PR?\n\nI was thinking this could be lumped in https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/29083 with other stability changes.\n\n> Second, what is not critical to be split out from what?\n\nAh I was just saying that it was not critical to split off this sort of boilerplate changes from #29083 to make it easier to review. \n\n> Also, what's about inheritance by default?\n\nI personally like the motto that unstable inherits and everything stable must be annotated as such, it gives convenient behavior where expected and requires work where expected as well!\n",
